$ PowerShell: Multithreaded Web Server

For a project running in a Windows environment, I needed a → web/webserver.

Because the web server needed to be multithreaded and I wanted to start the threads with `→ Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/threadJob/start`, *PowerShell 7* is required to run the web server.

For future reference, the non-project related code is put to → https://github.com/ReneNyffenegger/ps7-multithreaded-webserver[github].

{ Source code

  The functionality fits into one file:
  gh|ps7-multithreaded-webserver|/webserver.ps1||

}
{ Starting the web server when the machine boots up

  The following commands can be used to start the webserver → Windows/PowerShell/command-inventory/noun/scheduledTask/register[when the machine boots up]:
code {
$wdr = 'C:/development/ps/webserver'
$act = new-scheduledTaskAction      -execute C:/development/ps/7.5.4/pwsh.exe -argument "-file $wdr/webserver.ps1" -workingDirectory $wdr
$trg = new-scheduledTaskTrigger     -atStartup
$prc = new-scheduledTaskPrincipal   -userId "NT AUTHORITY\SYSTEM" -logonType ServiceAccount
register-scheduledTask -taskName 'dashboard webserver' -taskPath \TQ84\Prj  -action $act -trigger $trg -settings $set -principal $prc
code }

}

sa:
 `→ Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Net/HttpListener` etc.
